<p>We now describe how to update our belief about the true state of the epidemic, denoted by Π(⋅), once new observations 
 <italic>y</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>
 </sub> are obtained. We first note that Π(⋅) is defined to return 1 for the most likely state 
 <inline-formula id="pcbi.1005257.e023">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1005257.e023.jpg" id="pcbi.1005257.e023g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M23">
    <mover accent="true">
     <mi>ν</mi>
     <mo>^</mo>
    </mover>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula>, and zero elsewhere. Therefore, given the state 
 <inline-formula id="pcbi.1005257.e024">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1005257.e024.jpg" id="pcbi.1005257.e024g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M24">
    <msub>
     <mover accent="true">
      <mi>ν</mi>
      <mo>^</mo>
     </mover>
     <mrow>
      <mi>i</mi>
      <mo>-</mo>
      <mn>1</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> at time 
 <italic>t</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>−1
 </sub>, the probability of observing 
 <italic>y</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>
 </sub> during the interval [
 <italic>t</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>−1
 </sub>, 
 <italic>t</italic>
 <sub>
  <italic>i</italic>
 </sub>] is equal to 
 <inline-formula id="pcbi.1005257.e025">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1005257.e025.jpg" id="pcbi.1005257.e025g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M25">
    <mrow>
     <mi>P</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <msub>
       <mi>y</mi>
       <mi>i</mi>
      </msub>
      <mo>|</mo>
      <msub>
       <mi>ν</mi>
       <mi>i</mi>
      </msub>
      <mo>,</mo>
      <msub>
       <mover accent="true">
        <mi>ν</mi>
        <mo>^</mo>
       </mover>
       <mrow>
        <mi>i</mi>
        <mo>-</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo>;</mo>
      <mi>θ</mi>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
     <mi>p</mi>
     <mrow>
      <mo>(</mo>
      <msub>
       <mi>ν</mi>
       <mi>i</mi>
      </msub>
      <mo>|</mo>
      <msub>
       <mover accent="true">
        <mi>ν</mi>
        <mo>^</mo>
       </mover>
       <mrow>
        <mi>i</mi>
        <mo>-</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
       </mrow>
      </msub>
      <mo>;</mo>
      <mi>θ</mi>
      <mo>)</mo>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> (see the discussion prior to 
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="pcbi.1005257.e008">Eq (3)</xref>).
</p>
